>Chris,,, I always recommend NOT turning the engine with the dist out.
>
>reason being,  you can have the drive lift up as you turn the engine, this can
>allow the shims to fall into the engine, but worse, it jams the gear, and 
>people
>can't figure out why the engine "seized"...  they tear it apart,, or scrap 
>it,,
>,,, or just get really frustrated till they find out the drive has lifted as
>they turned the engine,, the gears jammed, and bound up the crank.
